comments: Turner (IND) makes marginal contact to Covington's (MIN) chest, but the contact does not dislodge him.
During the pick, Warren (IND) initiates contact with Towns (MIN) that dislodges him from his legal position.
Wiggins (MIN) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Lamb (IND) after the release on his jump shot attempt.
Covington (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position in Lamb's (IND) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Sabonis (IND) makes marginal contact with Wiggins' (MIN) during his shooting motion and then cleanly blocks the shot attempt.
Warren (IND) briefly grasps Wiggins' (MIN) jersey as he goes to set the screen.
During the screen, Warren (IND) and Wiggins (MIN) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Towns (MIN) does not step out of bounds when he receives the pass or before he releases his three point shot attempt. The contact between him and Turner (IND) occurs after the whistle.
Culver (MIN) wraps Sabonis (IND) during the pick and affects his FOM.
Wiggins (MIN) makes marginal contact to Brogdon's (IND) arm during his drive.
Napier (MIN) cleanly steals the ball from Brogdon (IND).
Wiggins' (MIN) briefly grasps Brogdon's (IND) arm during his play at the basket, but the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to contest the shot.
Brogdon (IND) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the play at the basket by Wiggins (MIN).
Napier (MIN) and Warren (IND) both make a clean play for the ball in an attempt to tip the ball out on the rebound.
Culver (MIN) makes clean hand on ball contact to dislodge it from Warren (IND).
Covington (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position in Brogdon's (IND) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Wiggins (MIN) steps out of bounds when he receives the pass.
Okogie (MIN) has a resting hand on Brogdon's (IND) back and the contact is marginal during the driving shot attempt.
As Towns (MIN) firms up in a legal screening position, Warren (IND) wraps him and pulls him back.  The contact dislodges him from his legally obtained position.
There is no conclusive video evidence that shows if Wiggins (MIN) steps out of bounds while dribbling on the perimeter.

Warren (IND) cleanly takes the ball away from Covington (MIN) on the rebound. Subsequently, Covington gets two hands on the ball and a held ball is correctly whistled.  Indiana signals for a timeout when Covington already has his hands on the ball.

Wiggins (MIN) and Lamb (IND) engage and separate during the jump ball and the contact is marginal.  Lamb is able to cleanly retrieve the ball and start his transition play after the marginal contact from Wiggins and Covington (MIN).
Wiggins (MIN) briefly engages with Warren (IND) during the inbound, and as they separate Holiday (IND) throws the inbound pass off Covington (MIN), resulting in the clock expiring.
Napier (MIN) commits a take foul on Lamb (IND).
